EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to employment practices; prohibiting an employer,
with certain exceptions, from taking certain adverse
employment actions against an employee who declines to
attend certain meetings or participate in certain
communications where the purpose of the meeting or
communication is to communicate the opinion of the
employer regarding religious matters or political matters;
providing a penalty; and providing other matters properly
relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law establishes various unlawful employment practices. (Chapter 613
2 of NRS) This bill prohibits an employer from taking or threatening to take certain
3 adverse employment actions against an employee because the employee declines to
4 attend a meeting sponsored by the employer or declines to participate in, receive or
5 listen to any communication by the employer or an agent or representative thereof
6 where the purpose of the meeting or communication is to communicate the opinion
7 of the employer regarding religious or political matters. This bill provides an
8 exception from existing provisions concerning religious matters for a religious
9 corporation, association or society. (NRS 613.320) Under this bill, an employer
10 who violates the provisions of this bill is guilty of a misdemeanor.
