THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 613 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
2 thereto a new section to read as follows:
3 1. Except as otherwise provided in subsection 2, it is unlawful
4 for any employer in this State to discharge, discipline,
5 discriminate, retaliate or take any other adverse employment
6 action against, or threaten to take any such action against, an
7 employee because the employee declines to attend a meeting
8 sponsored by the employer or declines to participate in, receive
9 or listen to any communication by the employer or an agent or
10 representative thereof where the purpose of the meeting or
11 communication is to communicate the opinion of the employer
12 regarding:
13 (a) Religious matters; or
14 (b) Political matters.
15 2. The provisions of paragraph (a) of subsection 1 do not
16 apply to an employer described in paragraph (b) of subsection 1 of
17 NRS 613.320.
18 3. An employer who violates the provisions of subsection 1 is
19 guilty of a misdemeanor.
20 4. As used in this section:
21 (a) “Political matters” means matters relating to elections for
22 political office, political parties, proposals to change legislation or
23 regulations or the decision to join or support any political party or
24 political, civic, community, fraternal or labor organization.
25 (b) “Religious matters” means matters relating to religious
26 affiliation or practice or the decision to join or support any
27 religious organization or association.
